** Carnage was somewhat glad to see that Teltoli had cheered, her eyes never 
strayed from Instrat.**
" What does that mean now, we're related?"
** She said this in a lighthearted sarcastic tone even though danger may be 
threatening.
There had been enough arguing.
Carnage heard Teltoli trandform into her robot mode, but remained in beast 
mode herself...for now. She might have to call upon her guns soon and that 
called for a transformation. Though she was more eager to get home then 
fight it out with Instrat.
Carnage glanced over her shoulder towards Teltoli and flashed her a look 
which spoke that it wasn't wise to act too haisty, they had plenty of time 
to beat this bot if it came down to it.
She then turned her head back only to find herself nose to snout with 
Instrat, growing and jerking her head back in irder to focus on her face 
properly. Once that was done Carnage growled at Instrat, her teeth inches 
away from the fems face, her body not even moving an inch from where it had 
originally been.**
" Just hold on here! If you would care to notice that life isn't perfect and 
no one is perfect either."
** Carnage pointed a claw tipped finger towards Instrat.**
" As I recall a sertain female who was suddenly about to whack my head off 
in a clearing back there just because I was trying to get dinner. Then you 
realized your mistake. MISTAKE!
Even YOU make mistakes, just like Teltoli had. So you see, no ones perfect, 
including me."
** Carnage growled and moved towards the pigs on the ground, throwing them 
onto her back before moving around Instrat with a growl.**
" Come on Teltoli, we gotta get home."
** She would leave their guest to the storm.**
